item.title: Frankfurt airport faces disruptions due to air traffic system fault
item.description: Frankfurt Airport warned of potential flight delays and cancellations due to a technical problem with the German traffic control system. The issue, affecting data transmission nationwide and other hubs like Dusseldorf, was resolved later. Travellers were advised to check flight statuses as Frankfurt, Germany's busiest airport, experienced technical faults starting from 10 a.m.

item.title: EAM Jaishankar's Sri Lanka visit commences on Friday, says 'good to be in Colombo again'
item.description: External Affairs Minister S Jaishankar arrives in Sri Lanka to engage with the new leadership, marking the first official visit since their presidential election. The visit aligns with India's Neighbourhood First Policy and SAGAR outlook, focusing on strengthening bilateral ties and collaboration across various platforms.

item.title: Heroic passengers unite to protect woman from assault on flight
item.description: Passengers and flight attendants on an American Airlines flight from Miami to Charlotte intervened when a man allegedly assaulted a woman in first class. Multiple passengers confronted the man, and upon arrival in Charlotte, local law enforcement escorted both individuals off the plane. The incident is under investigation.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: FEMA faces funding shortage for Hurricane relief, critics blame migrant aid
item.description: Homeland Security Secretary Alejandro Mayorkas revealed that FEMA lacks sufficient funds for the Atlantic hurricane season. Criticism arose due to FEMA's $640.9 million allocation this year for asylum seeker assistance. Republican lawmakers like Texas Governor Greg Abbott demand redirecting funds to disaster relief amid Hurricane Helene's devastation, highlighting the political tension over federal spending priorities.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Watch: Two moms turn children's playground into MMA arena as they exchange punches, kicks
item.description: Two mothers caused chaos at a children's indoor playground in China by getting into a violent fight in a ball pit. The confrontation involved hair-pulling and kicking as shocked onlookers, including other parents and children, watched. Some tried to intervene, highlighting the unpredictable tensions that can emerge in public spaces designed for family fun.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Meghan's 'vanished' ring worries Prince William back home: 'It has set off alarm bells'
item.description: Prince William is reportedly concerned about the disappearance of Princess Diana’s jewelry pieces previously held by Meghan Markle. Among these is Meghan’s engagement ring, which Harry designed using Diana’s diamonds. The ring hasn't been seen recently, raising questions and worries about preserving Diana’s legacy, especially from Prince William.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Princess Kate helps fulfill bucket list wish of 16-year-old cancer patient, shares emotional hug
item.description: Liz Hatton, a 16-year-old with terminal cancer, met the Princess of Wales at Windsor Castle, where she was praised for her photography. This encounter was part of fulfilling Hatton's photography bucket list, shared by her mother to create cherished memories in her remaining time.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Student 'ruthlessly tackled' for failing to tap his travel card on bus in Australia
item.description: A student allegedly encountered excessive force by transport officers on a Melbourne bus for not tapping his Myki travel card. Videos show the student pinned and gasping for air, while officers restrained him, sparking online outrage. Police responded, arresting a man but did not mention the Myki card issue. An investigation is underway.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: What Trump said on wife Melania backing abortion rights in new memoir
item.description: Former President Donald Trump expressed support for Melania Trump's public declaration in her upcoming memoir, where she backs abortion rights, differing from his conservative stance. Trump emphasised the importance of sticking to one's convictions, while Melania advocates for individual freedom and a woman's right to control her body.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Will be there to ...': Elon Musk set to attend Trump’s rally at July assassination attempt site
item.description: Elon Musk has confirmed his attendance at Donald Trump’s upcoming Pennsylvania rally. Following a previous assassination attempt on Trump in Butler, the event will have heightened security measures. This rally aims to mobilize voters in the crucial swing state, amid a tight race with Democratic candidate Kamala Harris.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Was Jennifer Aniston secretly dating Barack Obama? Actress responds
item.description: Jennifer Aniston used her appearance on ‘Jimmy Kimmel Live’ to humorously debunk tabloid rumors, including a false romance with Barack Obama and her unconventional beauty treatments. She also shared unique personal anecdotes, such as traveling with jars of olives and her therapist's ashes, and reflected on her childhood and family traditions.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'You bear responsibility of ...': Houthis warn shipowners in new phase of escalating Red Sea attacks
item.description: Greek shipping companies have been receiving serious threats from Yemen's Houthi militia regarding their vessels in the Red Sea. The Houthis, citing a transit ban violation involving an Israeli port, have warned of targeted attacks. These threats have caused significant route changes and elevated insurance rates, impacting international shipping and trade in the region.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Vance breaks down his viral ‘Jim Halpert’ side-smirk moment at VP debate
item.description: Ohio Senator JD Vance's frequent glances at the camera during the vice presidential debate sparked viral comparisons to 'The Office' character Jim Halpert, despite Vance's claims of unintentionality. Despite his admitted nervousness, he felt affirmed by his wife's positive reaction following the debate.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Trump most dangerous candidate': Bruce Springsteen joins celebrity list backing Kamala Harris
item.description: Bruce Springsteen publicly endorses Kamala Harris for the upcoming presidential election, emphasizing the dangers posed by her opponent, Donald Trump. Springsteen's support follows endorsements from other prominent celebrities, reflecting widespread backing from Hollywood for Harris and her running mate, Tim Walz.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: MrBeast discloses secret plan to keep uploading videos after death
item.description: YouTube’s biggest star, MrBeast, disclosed on Logan Paul's podcast that he has pre-recorded 15 videos to be uploaded posthumously. Although he admits the content is subpar, the intention is to keep his channel active after his death. With 318 million subscribers, MrBeast aims to continue surprising his audience even beyond his lifetime.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: US dock workers end strike after 3 days, reach agreement to boost wages by 62%
item.description: Longshore workers in the U.S. end a major work stoppage with a new agreement including a 62% wage hike over six years, raising hourly wages to $63. The strike, affecting 45,000 workers, halted operations at 36 ports and caused significant supply disruptions. The contract extends until January 2025 to address remaining issues.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Worst is yet to come’: Living ‘Nostradamus’ warned of Middle East conflict—and it’s happening
item.description: Brazilian psychic Athos Salomé warned of escalating conflict between Israel and Iran, predicting a global crisis. He highlighted the potential role of AI and electromagnetic pulse attacks in future hostilities. Salomé foresees geopolitical strife spreading beyond the Middle East, destabilizing the world.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Diabolically smart tbh': Elon Musk accuses Democrats of flipping swing states with illegal immigration
item.description: Elon Musk accused the Democratic Party of intentionally increasing illegal immigration to swing states for voter importation, fast-tracking migrants to citizenship. He shared data highlighting significant rises in illegal immigrant populations in key states since 2021, criticising the Biden administration's immigration policies.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Outrage in SA over farmers accused of feeding slain black women to pigs
item.description: Two black women seeking discarded food on a white-owned farm in Limpopo Province were fatally shot, and their decomposed bodies were found in a pigsty, igniting debates over race, gender-based violence, and land tensions in South Africa. The accused include the farm owner, a supervisor, and a worker.

item.title: Top Republican urges Biden to rush 2,000-pound bombs to Israel held up over human rights concerns
item.description: US Representative Michael McCaul urges President Biden to expedite delayed 2,000-pound bomb shipments to Israel due to rising regional tensions and threats from Hamas and Hezbollah. The shipments have been stalled due to human rights concerns over civilian casualties in Gaza. Biden administration's response remains pending.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk
